---
kind: rule
version: "1.0"
description: xcaffold authoring conventions. Apply when creating or editing .xcaf files.
activation: always
name: xcaf-conventions
---
When authoring or editing xcaffold `.xcaf` files, follow these conventions:

## Field naming

- Use kebab-case for all field names: `allowed-tools`, `always-apply`, `permission-mode`
- Never use camelCase or snake_case in xcaf files

## Version quoting

- Always quote version: `version: "1.0"` not `version: 1.0`
- Bare numbers are parsed as floats and will fail validation

## Name pattern

- name must match `^[a-z0-9-]+$` — lowercase letters, digits, hyphens only
- No uppercase, no underscores, no spaces

## Directory layout

- One resource per file
- Use directory-per-resource: `xcaf/<kind>/<name>/<name>.xcaf`
- Example: `xcaf/agents/my-agent/my-agent.xcaf`
- Per-provider overrides: `xcaf/agents/<name>/agent.<provider>.xcaf`

## Field correctness by kind

- agent: use `tools:` (not `allowed-tools:`)
- skill: use `allowed-tools:` (not `tools:`)
- hooks: pure YAML format — no `---` frontmatter delimiters
- memory: content comes from file body, not a `content:` field
- mcp: no body and no targets (per-provider overrides not supported)

## Never do

- Never write directly to `.claude/`, `.cursor/`, `.gemini/`, `.github/`, or `.agents/`
- Those directories are xcaffold output — owned by `xcaffold apply`
- Always edit `xcaf/` files and compile with `xcaffold apply`
